<li><a href="http://www.fooledbyrandomness.com/fortune.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.fooledbyrandomness.com/fortune.pdf" rel="nofollow">"How the Finance Gurus Get Risk All Wrong"</a> by Benoit Mandelbrot &amp; Nassim Nicholas Taleb. <i>Fortune</i>, July 11, 2005.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.newyorker.com/fact/content/articles/060213fa_fact" class="external text" title="http://www.newyorker.com/fact/content/articles/060213fa_fact" rel="nofollow">"Million-dollar Murray":</a> power-law distributions in homelessness and other social problems; by Malcolm Gladwell. <i>The New Yorker</i>, February 13, 2006.</li>
<li>Benoit Mandelbrot &amp; Richard Hudson: <cite>The Misbehaviour of Markets (2004)</cite></li>
<li>Philip Ball: <a href="http://www.agrfoto.com/philipball/criticalmass.php" class="external text" title="http://www.agrfoto.com/philipball/criticalmass.php" rel="nofollow">Critical Mass: How one thing leads to another</a> (2005)</li>
<li><a href="http://econophysics.blogspot.com/2006/07/tyranny-of-power-law-and-why-we-should.html" class="external text" title="http://econophysics.blogspot.com/2006/07/tyranny-of-power-law-and-why-we-should.html" rel="nofollow"><i>Tyranny of the Power Law</i></a> from <a href="http://econophysics.blogspot.com" class="external text" title="http://econophysics.blogspot.com" rel="nofollow">The Econophysics Blog</a></li>
